==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''coaxial cable'''
# A [[cable]] which consists of a thin conducting central wire surrounded mediately by an outer conducting cylindrical metal shield (coated outside with plastic) which protects the central wire from [[EMI]] but which is separated from the central wire by insulation immediately surrounding the central wire and lying concentrically between the central wire and the outer shield.  The modifier "coaxial" refers to the fact that the central wire and the outer shield are transversally concentric (i.e. coaxial).

